                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1167">In hagiography: Bassus and his twin sister <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1168">Suzanna</persName> 
                        were twin children of a Zoroastrian governor. They were informed about Christianity by a
                        Christian slave. They were baptized by an ascetic named <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1342">Longinus</persName>. They were killed by
                        their father. A martyr named <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1229">Stephen</persName> is also commemorated with them. At least one <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/571">monastery
                            commemorating Mar Bassus</placeName> was founded near <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/11">Apamea</placeName>.</note>
